    "to express the lensing result of small finite sources.",
    "The inverse Hessian (or inverse curvature) of the arrival time is a tensor magnification.",
    "It is called the magnification matrix.",
    "The inverse magnification matrix is conventionally separated into a trace and a traceless part.",
    "From the Poisson equation (37) it follows that the trace will be 1κ."
